{"id":"nucl-th/9908078","submitter":"Martin Effenberger","authors":"M. Effenberger and U. Mosel","title":"Photoproduction of mesons in nuclei at GeV energies","comments":"Text added in summary in general reliability of the method,\n  references updated. Phys. Rev. C (2000) in press","journal-ref":"Phys.Rev. C62 (2000) 014605","doi":"10.1103/PhysRevC.62.014605","report-no":"UGI-99-21","categories":"nucl-th hep-ph","license":null,"abstract":"  In a transport model that combines initial state interactions of the photon\nwith final state interactions of the produced particles we present a\ncalculation of inclusive photoproduction of mesons in nuclei in the energy\nrange from 1 to 7 GeV. We give predictions for the photoproduction cross\nsections of pions, etas, kaons, antikaons, and $\\pi^+\\pi^-$ invariant mass\nspectra in ^{12}C and ^{208}Pb. The effects of nuclear shadowing and final\nstate interaction of the produced particles are discussed in detail.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 27 Aug 1999 12:38:39 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 10 Nov 1999 18:24:43 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 7 Apr 2000 11:55:03 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-10-31"}
{"id":"quant-ph/9908079","submitter":"Martin Bojowald","authors":"Martin Bojowald and Thomas Strobl","title":"Group Theoretical Quantization and the Example of a Phase Space S^1 x\n  R^+","comments":"41 pages, LaTeX2e","journal-ref":"J.Math.Phys. 41 (2000) 2537-2567","doi":"10.1063/1.533258","report-no":"PITHA 99/25, ESI 742","categories":"quant-ph gr-qc hep-th","license":null,"abstract":"  The group theoretical quantization scheme is reconsidered by means of\nelementary systems. Already the quantization of a particle on a circle shows\nthat the standard procedure has to be supplemented by an additional condition\non the admissibility of group actions. A systematic strategy for finding\nadmissible group actions for particular subbundles of cotangent spaces is\ndeveloped, two-dimensional prototypes of which are T^*R^+ and S^1 x R^+\n(interpreted as restrictions of T^*R and T^*S^1 to positive coordinate and\nmomentum, respectively). In this framework (and under an additional, natural\ncondition) an SO_+(1,2)-action on S^1 x R^+ results as the unique admissible\ngroup action.\n  For symplectic manifolds which are (specific) parts of phase spaces with\nknown quantum theory a simple projection method of quantization is formulated.\nFor T^*R^+ and S^1 x R^+ equivalent results to those of more established (but\nmore involved) quantization schemes are obtained. The approach may be of\ninterest, e.g., in attempts to quantize gravity theories where demanding\nnondegenerate metrics of a fixed signature imposes similar constraints.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 27 Aug 1999 13:51:07 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 13 Dec 1999 13:33:43 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-09-08"}
